<subSubSection id="328AA876A95243C370C8F1D178DD9AB4" pageId="7" pageNumber="14" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="0A9A95E6C5928E3668E43B434A8B4024" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">Type</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C2E28E422107BCB1C9F7EE4E866C1E6" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">
(lectotype designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="C881B6AC25CBE32936D42DB062A9D319" author="Zohary, M" journalOrPublisher="The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" refId="B62" refString="Zohary, M, Heller, D, 1984. The Genus Trifolium. The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" title="The Genus Trifolium." year="1984">Zohary and Heller 1984</bibRefCitation>
: 274): In Gallia, Italia, Apulia. Hort. Clifford, 373, 7 (BM).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="489F14FAD266280E41015F12F263B097" pageId="7" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph id="B12E2D0ED3FFA19AB2EECAD309CE23E4" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="913681D0594373137BED68C263795303" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">
Flowering heads small (15-20 mm); fruiting calyx vesicular-turbinate, netted-nerved; corolla short, slightly protruding from the calyx (
<figureCitation id="8E98D66A5F7629B213DEECA7CB920D9D" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Comparison between mature calyces of Trifolium subsect. Mystillus species in Italy (bar = 1 mm). Left: Trifolium vesiculosum (A) and Trifolium spumosum (A '), middle Trifolium multistriatum transitional (B) and typical (B ') forms, right Trifolium mutabile s. str. (C) and Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum (C ')." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106589" pageId="7" pageNumber="14" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2">Figure 2A</figureCitation>
'), seed ovoid, light brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C90DDE3C70EA5C2092A28B156D3E8252" pageId="7" pageNumber="14" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="364FA0F0E975456D586D8875AC1A2D44" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">Updated geographical distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91E959FDF04F8ED3DD624AC3F5CF1B24" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">Liguria: 0 (new), Tuscany: 0 (new), Marche: 0, Lazio: +, Abruzzo: 0 (new), Campania: 0 (new), Apulia: 0 (new), Basilicata: 0 (new), Calabria: +, Sicily: +, Sardinia: +.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2D41AFDFED3C63E451CF57929D5C54BC" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="7" pageNumber="14" type="notes">
<paragraph id="7B66C0B657179BF632622752EF4C1FFA" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="935D74A67EECEAA0FBDBE0309AD56681" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">
It is a widespread steno-Mediterranean thermophilous and xerophilous species, especially found in dry uncultivated lands of coastal areas. It was described on the basis of collections made in Italy and France. Based on our data, the distribution in Italy is very fragmented and in decline, especially in the central regions. A similar depletion has been reported in southern France where the species is classified as naturalized over most of the territory (
<bibRefCitation id="187D76778E6465A37352C9ABE4CC2C39" author="Coulot, P" journalOrPublisher="Societe Botanique du Centre-Ouest, Jarnac" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B10" refString="Coulot, P, Rabaute, P, 2013. Monographie des Leguminosae de France. Tome 3. Tribu des Trifolieae. Societe Botanique du Centre-Ouest, Jarnac" title="Monographie des Leguminosae de France. Tome 3. Tribu des Trifolieae." year="2013">Coulot and Rabaute 2013</bibRefCitation>
). It is quite widespread in Sicily (
<bibRefCitation id="35E3C75E3682A555D0140DDEC170FAC5" author="Giardina, G" journalOrPublisher="Bocconea" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="181 - 182" refId="B22" refString="Giardina, G, Raimondo, F, Spadaro, V, 2007. A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily. Bocconea 20: 181 - 182" title="A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily." volume="20" year="2007">Giardina et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="99F42304CBB4047254139D78320866FA" author="La Rosa, A" journalOrPublisher="Universita degli Studi di Palermo" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" refId="B30" refString="La Rosa, A, 2011. Indagini tassonomiche, ecologiche e distributive sul genere Trifolium L. in Sicilia. Universita degli Studi di Palermo" title="Indagini tassonomiche, ecologiche e distributive sul genere Trifolium L. in Sicilia" year="2011">La Rosa 2011</bibRefCitation>
), where it mostly grows in arid uncultivated hilly and mountain areas. However, its current presence in the Italian southern regions, especially in Campania and Apulia, has probably been underestimated due to confusion with other taxa (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="9EFDA8B9CC3EC46A1FEC4B71834F1540" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vesiculosum">
<emphasis id="0D924296C981CECC6DA87CC7A7C739A9" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">Trifolium vesiculosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E3FE6D532F94474980FA1C8230FDB556" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium resupinatum" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="resupinatum">
<emphasis id="FE8926042C58736FCDC01E1BD6F9D48A" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">Trifolium resupinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="95BA51D37B7C4EF2B591E2497491E0D0" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">
<bibRefCitation id="5CE51C4D443DAB6874DFC091B54FB970" author="Peccenini, S" editor="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Informatore Botanico Italiano" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="426 - 427" refId="B44" refString="Peccenini, S, 2007. Notulae: 1381-1383. In: Conti, F, Nepi, C, Peruzzi, L, Scoppola, A, Eds., Notulae alla checklist della flora vascolare italiana 4 (1311-1419). . Informatore Botanico Italiano 39: 426 - 427" title="Notulae: 1381 - 1383." volume="39" volumeTitle="Notulae alla checklist della flora vascolare italiana 4 (1311 - 1419)." year="2007">Peccenini (2007)</bibRefCitation>
cites the report by 
<bibRefCitation id="1F5B8D7B14B6DE61372AE792A77B5666" author="Bertoloni, A" journalOrPublisher="Masi, Bologna" pageId="12" pageNumber="19" refId="B1" refString="Bertoloni, A, 1850. Flora Italica. Masi, Bologna, 183 pp." title="Flora Italica" year="1850">Bertoloni (1850)</bibRefCitation>
&quot;ex Liguria orientali in litore Clavarensi a Turio; Genua 
<normalizedToken id="D9ACC5BD6CFE136C7AAF40B2F5EE34CC" originalValue="all’Acquasola">all'Acquasola</normalizedToken>
a Vincentio&quot; and by 
<bibRefCitation id="365C99A8FED490A2BF093EC374758C6D" author="Fiori, A" journalOrPublisher="Nuova Flora Analitica d'Italia" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="859 - 860" refId="B17" refString="Fiori, A, 1925. . Nuova Flora Analitica d'Italia 1: 859 - 860" volume="1" year="1925">Fiori (1925)</bibRefCitation>
for Liguria; moreover her recent report in the outskirts of Sarzana (FI!, GE; 
<bibRefCitation id="58585F128266DD81AEB26871FB0A3E33" author="Peccenini, S" editor="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Informatore Botanico Italiano" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="426 - 427" refId="B44" refString="Peccenini, S, 2007. Notulae: 1381-1383. In: Conti, F, Nepi, C, Peruzzi, L, Scoppola, A, Eds., Notulae alla checklist della flora vascolare italiana 4 (1311-1419). . Informatore Botanico Italiano 39: 426 - 427" title="Notulae: 1381 - 1383." volume="39" volumeTitle="Notulae alla checklist della flora vascolare italiana 4 (1311 - 1419)." year="2007">Peccenini 2007</bibRefCitation>
) must be corrected, as the sample actually refers to 
<taxonomicName id="CB6B725A5F25922C45522C2BB0FF5F41" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium resupinatum" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="resupinatum">
<emphasis id="8016E707B78401D8890A9F6DB83C78BA" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">Trifolium resupinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, we record the species as requiring confirmation in Liguria. Concerning Tuscany, no herbarium material can confirm the historical records of this species between Grosseto and Castiglione della Pescaia (Savi in 
<bibRefCitation id="FCE08CD15B8AB3F8628A58A8B10AF529" author="Caruel, T" journalOrPublisher="Firenze" pageId="12" pageNumber="19" pagination="168 - 169" refId="B5" refString="Caruel, T, 1862. Prodromo della Flora Toscana. Firenze: 168 - 169" title="Prodromo della Flora Toscana" year="1862">Caruel 1862</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="78EE68E5DCF13CA7C8E66181DA24FDA0" author="Pignatti, S" journalOrPublisher="Edagricole, Bologna" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="721 - 741" refId="B45" refString="Pignatti, S, 1982. Flora d'Italia. Edagricole, Bologna: 721 - 741" title="Flora d'Italia" year="1982">Pignatti 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C90249D37DFD392DF363611A2830CF29" author="Selvi, F" journalOrPublisher="Flora Mediterranea" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" pagination="47 - 139" refId="B51" refString="Selvi, F, 2010. A critical checklist of the vascular flora of Tuscan Maremma (Grosseto province, Italy). Flora Mediterranea 20: 47 - 139" title="A critical checklist of the vascular flora of Tuscan Maremma (Grosseto province, Italy)." volume="20" year="2010">Selvi 2010</bibRefCitation>
), but several specimens from the Elba, Giglio, and Pianosa islands (FI!) confirm its presence in the past. Also in need of confirmation is its occurrence in Marche, where it was collected in Senigallia (Ancona) in 1876 (FI! as 
<taxonomicName id="7F339162C8664A040E4B46D0D7AD0233" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vesiculosum">
<emphasis id="C05795096D8418915BCB262D8E00EB8F" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="14">Trifolium vesiculosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="80D8034DBED3634E95CD1AFBB8C0EE0D" author="Gubellini, L" journalOrPublisher="Informatore Botanico Italiano" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="17 - 26" refId="B26" refString="Gubellini, L, Hofmann, N, Pinzi, M, 2014. Contributo alla conoscenza della flora vascolare delle Marche e di alcune regioni limitrofe. Informatore Botanico Italiano 46: 17 - 26" title="Contributo alla conoscenza della flora vascolare delle Marche e di alcune regioni limitrofe." volume="46" year="2014">Gubellini et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). The occurrence of the species in Abruzzo (
<bibRefCitation id="AF60728F4BE03F16797970F967B5CD94" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Bocconea" pageId="12" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 276" refId="B7" refString="Conti, F, 1998. An annotated check-list to the flora of the Abruzzo. Bocconea 10: 1 - 276" title="An annotated check-list to the flora of the Abruzzo." volume="10" year="1998">Conti 1998</bibRefCitation>
) is by 
<bibRefCitation id="044EAEEDD0181EAAA07999139F9A408B" author="Zodda, G" journalOrPublisher="Webbia" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 317" publicationUrl="10.1080/00837792.1954.10669624" refId="B60" refString="Zodda, G, 1954. La Flora Teramana. Webbia 10: 1 - 317" title="La Flora Teramana." url="10.1080/00837792.1954.10669624" volume="10" year="1954">Zodda (1954)</bibRefCitation>
and by 
<bibRefCitation id="7EF317910B4F9F07345CE7E2C52A652A" author="Crugnola, G" journalOrPublisher="G. Fabbri ed., Teramo" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B12" refString="Crugnola, G, 1894. La vegetazione al Gran Sasso d'Italia. G. Fabbri ed., Teramo" title="La vegetazione al Gran Sasso d'Italia" year="1894">Crugnola (1894</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F4612D562341AADD77263BBEE395E0AE" author="Crugnola, G" journalOrPublisher="Giornale Botanico Italiano" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="233 - 247" refId="B13" refString="Crugnola, G, 1900. Materiali per la flora dell'Abruzzo teramano. Un secondo manipolo di piante del Gran Sasso d'Italia. Giornale Botanico Italiano 7: 233 - 247" title="Materiali per la flora dell'Abruzzo teramano. Un secondo manipolo di piante del Gran Sasso d'Italia." volume="7" year="1900">1900</bibRefCitation>
) who refers to a sample by Petrilli from the Mavone valley (Valle del Vomano, Teramo); we have been unable to trace it. The occurrence in Campania and Basilicata (
<bibRefCitation id="FFF8C710FD2E472EE9C6720470AFC28F" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Palombi Editori, Roma" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B8" refString="Conti, F, Abbate, G, Alessandrini, A, Blasi, C, 2005. An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Palombi Editori, Roma" title="An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora." year="2005">Conti et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
) is only based on historical records from the outskirts of Avellino, &quot;Ad Aiello del Sabato&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="73072D0B73C306624024F60AA3E1E8B2" author="Milani, GB" journalOrPublisher="Avellino" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" refId="B39" refString="Milani, GB, 1890. Elenco di Piante del Principato Ultra. Avellino" title="Elenco di Piante del Principato Ultra" year="1890">Milani 1890</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="308350C02664A6D0AFC03ECEBCF9098A" author="Casali, C" journalOrPublisher="Pergola, Avellino" pageId="12" pageNumber="19" refId="B6" refString="Casali, C, 1901. Flora Irpina. R. Scuola di Viticoltura ed Enologia di Avellino. Tipografia E. Pergola, Avellino" title="Flora Irpina. R. Scuola di Viticoltura ed Enologia di Avellino. Tipografia E." year="1901">Casali 1901</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A1CD95B7DEC0A1B665E55056D7CBC92A" author="Trotter, A" journalOrPublisher="Bullettino della Societa Botanica Italiana" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" pagination="20 - 32" refId="B57" refString="Trotter, A, 1905. Osservazioni ed aggiunte alla Flora Irpina. Bullettino della Societa Botanica Italiana 1905: 20 - 32" title="Osservazioni ed aggiunte alla Flora Irpina." volume="1905" year="1905">Trotter 1905</bibRefCitation>
) and Caserta at S. Silvestro (
<bibRefCitation id="3198E0A2C9B9AFAA326F95C129A57E50" author="Terracciano, N" journalOrPublisher="Nobile e C., Caserta" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" refId="B54" refString="Terracciano, N, 1872. Relazione intorno alle peregrinazioni botaniche fatte per disposizione della Deputazione Provinciale di Terra di Lavoro in certi luoghi della provincia dal Dottor N. Terracciano. Nobile e C., Caserta" title="Relazione intorno alle peregrinazioni botaniche fatte per disposizione della Deputazione Provinciale di Terra di Lavoro in certi luoghi della provincia dal Dottor N. Terracciano." year="1872">Terracciano 1872</bibRefCitation>
) and on a gathering from an unknown locality by Tenore (NAP; A. Santangelo, pers. com.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="79D1E1B000A7877DB42DA917C59A8C62" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">
<pageBreakToken id="11ABCF091FE95C9693CADDBC44997762" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" start="start">The</pageBreakToken>
Apulian material dating back to the 1970s, deposited in PAD and labeled as 
<taxonomicName id="28B90488E7CAE1B49A56A2A9EE6616CF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium spumosum" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spumosum">
<emphasis id="70A8824803F9F39526550F9CED17BD54" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">Trifolium spumosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, actually refers to 
<taxonomicName id="ED9C018FF93AAEAA48E81FDFBF608291" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium resupinatum" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="resupinatum">
<emphasis id="8AD64BE8FB6A25C7962CB3BD07597FCF" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">Trifolium resupinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="48096998AACC3D1C45C793B46CF10AD0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium spumosum" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spumosum">
<emphasis id="089BF7A3ADB347EBFC8C6D776748EBF6" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">Trifolium spumosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reported from Apulia by 
<bibRefCitation id="AAD2C20B23CD36725B3409F7B31906BF" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Palombi Editori, Roma" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B8" refString="Conti, F, Abbate, G, Alessandrini, A, Blasi, C, 2005. An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Palombi Editori, Roma" title="An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora." year="2005">Conti et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
based on these gatherings and on 
<bibRefCitation id="A3B6DE1835579A38E497A4C2FA8F97A3" author="Bertoloni, A" journalOrPublisher="Masi, Bologna" pageId="12" pageNumber="19" refId="B1" refString="Bertoloni, A, 1850. Flora Italica. Masi, Bologna, 183 pp." title="Flora Italica" year="1850">Bertoloni (1850)</bibRefCitation>
, who cited a specimen collected in Foggia by Gussone (NAP!). The species is also reported in Salento by 
<bibRefCitation id="786809A7696E22470DF22794BCFB5174" author="Bruni, A" journalOrPublisher="Stamperia e Cartiere del Fibreno, Napoli" pageId="12" pageNumber="19" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.9655" refId="B4" refString="Bruni, A, 1857. Descrizione botanica delle campagne di Barletta. Stamperia e Cartiere del Fibreno, Napoli" title="Descrizione botanica delle campagne di Barletta" url="10.5962/bhl.title.9655" year="1857">Bruni (1857)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="4836CD6BE64911AB4890E3D73BB80374" author="Marinosci, M" journalOrPublisher="Ed. Salentina, Lecce" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" refId="B36" refString="Marinosci, M, 1870. La Flora Salentina. Ed. Salentina, Lecce" title="La Flora Salentina" year="1870">Marinosci (1870)</bibRefCitation>
, confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation id="8C31608578A1875DB36742F45188E9C6" author="Mele, C" journalOrPublisher="Flora Mediterranea" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="193 - 245" refId="B38" refString="Mele, C, Medagli, P, Accogli, R, Beccarisi, L, Albano, A, Marchiori, S, 2006. Flora of Salento (Apulia, Southeastern Italy): an annotated checklist. Flora Mediterranea 16: 193 - 245" title="Flora of Salento (Apulia, Southeastern Italy): an annotated checklist." volume="16" year="2006">Mele et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
and - for the Province of Brindisi - by 
<bibRefCitation id="5E6CCE168A2F8C6548BE91600C1EFEAA" author="Tomaselli, V" journalOrPublisher="Quaderni di Botanica Ambientale Applicata" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" pagination="53 - 76" refId="B56" refString="Tomaselli, V, Urbano, M, Sciandrello, S, Wagensommer, RP, Costanzo, E, Albano, A, Medagli, P, Mele, C, Di Pietro, R, 2010. Cartografia tematica ed analisi del paesaggio vegetale ed agricolo del Parco Naturale Regionale &quot;Saline di Punta della Contessa&quot; (Brindisi - Puglia). Quaderni di Botanica Ambientale Applicata 21: 53 - 76" title="Cartografia tematica ed analisi del paesaggio vegetale ed agricolo del Parco Naturale Regionale &quot; Saline di Punta della Contessa &quot; (Brindisi - Puglia)." volume="21" year="2010">Tomaselli et al. (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. As no recent samples were found either in LEC or BI (P. Medagli and V. Tomaselli, pers. com.), we still consider the species in need of confirmation for the current Apulian flora. The presence in Lazio, Calabria, and Sardinia (
<bibRefCitation id="3137DAFFF5823172EA55DC52F97955AE" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Palombi Editori, Roma" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B8" refString="Conti, F, Abbate, G, Alessandrini, A, Blasi, C, 2005. An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Palombi Editori, Roma" title="An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora." year="2005">Conti et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
) is confirmed.
</paragraph>
